6 Section 6. KRS 337.010 is amended to read as follows:
7 (1) As used in this chapter, unless the context requires otherwise:
8 (a) "Commissioner" means the commissioner of the Department of Workplace
9 Standards under the direction and supervision of the secretary of the
10 Education and Labor Cabinet;
11 (b) "Department" means the Department of Workplace Standards in the
12 Education and Labor Cabinet;
13 (c) 1. "Wages" includes any compensation due to an employee by reason of
14 his or her employment, including salaries, commissions, vested vacation
15 pay, overtime pay, severance or dismissal pay, earned bonuses, and any
16 other similar advantages agreed upon by the employer and the employee
17 or provided to employees as an established policy. The wages shall be
18 payable in legal tender of the United States, checks on banks, direct
19 deposits, or payroll card accounts convertible into cash on demand at
20 full face value, subject to the allowances made in this chapter. However,
21 an employee may not be charged an activation fee and the payroll card
22 account shall provide the employee with the ability, without charge, to
23 make at least one (1) withdrawal per pay period for any amount up to
24 and including the full account balance.
25 2. For the purposes of calculating hourly wage rates for scheduled
26 overtime for professional firefighters, as defined in KRS 95A.210(8),
27 "wages" shall not include the distribution to qualified professional
