1 firefighters by local governments of supplements received from the
2 Firefighters Foundation Program Fund. For the purposes of calculating
3 hourly wage rates for unscheduled overtime for professional firefighters,
4 as defined in KRS 95A.210(9), "wages" shall include the distribution to
5 qualified professional firefighters by local governments of supplements
6 received from the Firefighters Foundation Program Fund;
7 (d) "Employer" is any person, either individual, corporation, partnership, agency,
8 or firm who employs an employee and includes any person, either individual,
9 corporation, partnership, agency, or firm acting directly or indirectly in the
10 interest of an employer in relation to an employee; and
11 (e) "Employee" is any person employed by or suffered or permitted to work for
12 an employer, except that:
13 1. Notwithstanding any voluntary agreement entered into between the
14 United States Department of Labor and a franchisee, neither a franchisee
15 nor a franchisee's employee shall be deemed to be an employee of the
16 franchisor for any purpose under this chapter; and
17 2. Notwithstanding any voluntary agreement entered into between the
18 United States Department of Labor and a franchisor, neither a franchisor
19 nor a franchisor's employee shall be deemed to be an employee of the
20 franchisee for any purpose under this chapter.
21 For purposes of this paragraph, "franchisee" and "franchisor" have the same
22 meanings as in 16 C.F.R. sec. 436.1.
23 (2) As used in KRS 337.275 to 337.325, 337.345, and 337.385 to 337.405, unless the
24 context requires otherwise:
25 (a) "Employee" is any person employed by or suffered or permitted to work for
26 an employer, but shall not include:
27 1. Any individual employed in agriculture;
