7 Section 7. KRS 337.065 is amended to read as follows:
8 (1) No employer shall require an employee to remit to the employer any gratuity, or
9 any portion thereof, except for the purpose of withholding amounts required by
10 federal or state law. The amount withheld from such gratuity shall not exceed the
11 amount required by federal or state law.
12 (2) As used in this section, "gratuity" means voluntary monetary contribution received
13 by an employee from a guest, patron, or customer for services rendered.
14 (3) An employer may provide custodial services for the safekeeping of funds placed in
15 a tip pool mandated by the employer or voluntarily entered into amongst the
16 employees, if the account is properly identified and segregated from his other
17 business records and open to examination by pool participants.
18 (4) A tip pooling arrangement may include tipped employees. A tip pooling
19 arrangement shall not include salaried employees, managers, or supervisors.
20 Section 8. Whereas it is important that employers and employees have clear
21 rules regarding the permissibility of tip pools following changes in the interpretation of
22 federal agency rules, an emergency is declared to exist, and this Act takes effect upon its
23 passage and approval by the Governor or upon its otherwise becoming a law.
